name: Document Section
type: Core/Marker
description: |
  Marker contract that identifies a logical section of a document and links that section to the fields and contracts
  responsible for it. A section gives humans, agents, and change-management workflows a coherent unit of meaning such as
  payment setup, shipping details, consent terms, participant configuration, or embedded-order handling.

  `title` and `summary` describe the section in user-facing terms. `relatedFields` lists absolute document pointers for
  state fields covered by the section. `relatedContracts` lists same-scope contract keys that implement, enforce, or
  affect the section. Section-aware workflows use this information to group proposed contract changes, validate that
  contract edits belong to the right section, and present changes for review.

  Document Section is metadata with runtime relevance only for workflows that understand it. It is also identity-bearing
  document content. Changing a section's title, summary, fields, or related contracts changes what the document says
  about its own structure and review surface.
title:
  type: Text
  description: Short, human-readable title shown in UI summaries.
summary:
  type: Text
  description: Brief functional summary of the section's purpose and behavior.
relatedFields:
  type: List
  itemType: Text
  description: Absolute JSON Pointer paths of fields covered by this section.
relatedContracts:
  type: List
  itemType: Text
  description: Contract keys in the same scope that implement or affect the section.
